==English==

===Verb===
''to'' '''[[get]] [[away]] [[with]]'''

#{{idiom}} To do something which is [[prohibited]], [[forbidden]] or generally not [[allowed]], and not be [[punished]] for the action
#:''Do you think we could '''get away with''' taking Dad’s car?''
#:''Not many people '''get away with''' stealing that much money.''
#:''Our teacher’s so strict, he'd never let us '''get away with''' anything in class.''

''past tense'': '''[[got]] away with''', '''[[gotten]] away with'''
#To have done something prohibited and not be punished
#:''He was the ring leader.  Him and his crew snuck in to the building, stole the bathtub, and '''got away with''' it.  Imagine stealing a bathtub in broad daylight and we can't even prove it.  Basically it looks like he will have '''gotten away with''' it after all.''


